Phase Vocoder¶

Test of phase vocoder with identity phase locking. The identity phase locking preserves the intra-sinusoidal phase coherence.

The test is applied on 2 audio examples: sinewave and piano. Plots of the signals and the relative spectrograms are provided.

Bugs: Windowing: the amplitude of the stretched signal is halved respect to the original. Windowing: the beginning and the end have a different modulation of the rest of the stretched signal. IPython.display.Audio() displays a wrong duration, but the audio can be listened correctly.

In [26]:
import sys, os
import utils as U
from PV import phaseVocoder as PV
import IPython

#Audio files (to read and to write)
input1 = 'sounds/sine.wav'
output1 = 'PV/processed/sine_stretched_IPL.wav'
input2 = 'sounds/piano.wav'
output2 = 'PV/processed/piano_stretched_IPL.wav'

#Parameters of the Phase Vocoder
alpha = 1.5 # time stretching factor (1.5 is an expansion factor of half duration)
Hs = 512 # synthesis hop size
frameSize = 4096 
phaseLocking = 'identity'
